<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Depart1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Depart,</orth> subst. 1) a going away; always in the phrase <cit><quote>at my d.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 4, 96</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 1, 92</bibl>.<lb />2) death: <cit><quote>tidings were brought me of your loss and his d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 110</bibl></cit>.
